OL,3,CTributes to former Labour MP Doug
OL,4,CHoyle who has died aged 98
OL,6,FChorley MP and House of Commons
OL,7,FSpeaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle has
OL,8,Fannounced the death of his father, the
OL,9,Fformer North West Labour MP Doug Hoyle.
OL,11,FLord Doug Hoyle was aged 98 and passed
OL,12,Faway "peacefully at home with his
OL,13,Ffamily at his bedside".
OL,15,FDoug Hoyle served as MP for Nelson and
OL,16,FColne between 1974 and 1979, and then
OL,17,FWarrington from 1981 to 1997.
OL,19,FHe later joined the House of Lords
OL,20,Fwhere he served until the age of 97
OL,21,Fwhen he retired in 2023.
