OL,3,CTributes to former Labour MP Doug
OL,4,CHoyle who has died aged 98
OL,6,FSir Lindsay added: "Doug was a force
OL,7,Fto be reckoned with, first as MP for
OL,8,FNelson and Colne and then Warrington
OL,9,Fbefore he joined the House of Lords.
OL,11,F"He chaired the Parliamentary Labour
OL,12,FParty and was an outspoken member of
OL,13,Fthe ASTMS trade union, serving as
OL,14,Fpresident of both ASTMS and MSF."
OL,16,F"Doug loved his sport and as a massive
OL,17,Frugby league fan, became chairman of
OL,18,FWarrington Wolves in 1999, a position
OL,19,Fhe held with great passion and
OL,20,Fhonour," his son continued.
