OL,3,CTributes to former Labour MP Doug
OL,4,CHoyle who has died aged 98
OL,6,F"Today there is an empty armchair, an
OL,7,Fabsence of ready wit, and one less
OL,8,Fanimal lover in the world.
OL,10,F"Above all Doug was a family man and
OL,11,Fhe will be greatly missed by myself,
OL,12,FCatherine, Emma, the great
OL,13,Fgrandchildren and the whole family."
OL,15,FOne of Warrington's current MPs said
OL,16,FLord Hoyle was the town's "finest ever
OL,17,Fchampion".
